    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-10T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/9–1048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-10T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3546. For Jessup. You may inform Romulo and others US supporting his candidacy
                    for <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Vice-President.<note n="1" xml:id="d79fn1"
                        >This cable ended several weeks of memorandum-writing in the Department of
                        State as to how and for what United States support should be given to
                        General Romulo at the Third Session of the General Assembly. There were
                        elements in the Department who favored strongly a Romulo candidacy for the
                        presidency of the General Assembly.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
